@@bThe Zone A Southern Exit@@N~
@@bThe trail passes through a narrow gap between two large oaks whose roots have grown
together underground, heaving the earth between them into a low ridge. Beyond the
ridge, the trail continues south into the Bell-Fog zone — a stretch of the woodland
known for acoustic distortions and route drift. @@pSomething about the transition
feels deliberate, as if the woodland itself decided this was a threshold.@@N
