@@aThe Bell-Fog Entry@@N~
@@aThe transition into the Bell-Fog zone is marked by an immediate change in air quality:
cooler, heavier, with a faint mineral edge. @@aFog sits at knee height even in midday,
pooling in the hollows between roots and obscuring the ground surface. @@bA shepherd-
priest bell post stands at the zone entry, its bell intact and surprisingly clear-
toned when struck — the first functional bell encountered on the route south.@@N
