depression in the woodland floor, perhaps thirty meters across, ringed by the
oldest trees in this part of the Eccentric Woodland. @@pFunerary markers
continue here but in a different tradition: horizontal slabs rather than standing
stones, each carved with a name and a single image. @@pTallow smoke still
drifts from the south where the maze exhales into the basin air. @@pThe light
filters differently through the ancient canopy overhead — dimmer, more amber.@@N
