#7384
marrow ledger ninth acre boss woodland~
@@pthe Marrow Ledger of Ninth Acre@@N~
@@pThe Marrow Ledger of Ninth Acre waits at the lowest point of the basin, silent.@@N
~
@@pThe Marrow Ledger is not a creature in the conventional sense. It is the accumulated
memorial weight of the Ninth Acre tradition, given form by generations of funerary
ritual. It does not speak. It catalogs. Individuals who enter the Marrow Seam report
afterward that they remember things differently: some memories sharper, some replaced.
The Ledger does not distinguish between what should be remembered and what should not.@@N
~
